## @cmd-sync-jira

Goal: Make Jira → execution loop frictionless.

When invoked:
1) Use Atlassian MCP to fetch Thesis-related Jira issues from project **TQ (Thesis - QA)**:
   - Cloud ID: f97c7789-c9f8-4559-97e4-18d9d8c3845f
   - Project Key: TQ
   - Project Name: Thesis - QA
   - statuses: To Do, In Progress, Blocked (or your equivalents)
   - include key, title, status, priority, assignee, last updated

2) If issues exist:
   - Propose the top 1–3 tasks to work on next (ranked).
   - For each: give a brief rationale and a crisp “Definition of Done” (3–7 bullets).
   - Update `docs/PROJECT.md` section “Next Up (from Jira)” to reflect the ranked list.

3) If no issues exist:
   - Propose a short plan discussion (2–5 bullet agenda).
   - Draft 2–4 Jira issues (titles + descriptions + acceptance criteria).
   - After creation, update `docs/PROJECT.md` “Next Up” with the newly created issues.

Constraints:
- Do NOT write implementation code during sync.
- Do NOT mark work as done unless Jira says it’s done.
